i-builds-first-chip-with-broadcom-tsmc-scales-back-foundry-ambition-2024-10=
-29/ ) , after flirting with the idea of building its own fabs. The latter =
isn=E2=80=99t viable for a software company in a world where TSMC exists, b=
ut it is for the U.S. government if it=E2=80=99s serious about domestic cap=
abilities continuing to exist. The same story applies to Google, Amazon, Mi=
crosoft, and Meta.

To that end, the U.S. government could fund an independent Intel foundry =
=E2=80=94 spin out the product group along with the clueless board to Broad=
com or Qualcomm or private equity =E2=80=94 and provide price support for m=
odel builders to design and buy their chips there. Or, if the U.S. governme=
nt wanted to build the whole sandwich, it could directly fund model builder=
s =E2=80=94=C2=A0including one developed in-house =E2=80=94 and dictate tha=
t they not just use but deeply integrate with Intel-fabricated integrated c=
hips (it=E2=80=99s not out of the question that a fully integrated stack mi=
ght actually be the optimal route to AGI).

